{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper and set aside.","Place white sugar into mixing bowl and mill <b>4 sec\/speed 9<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place 30 g of the pistachio nuts into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside (omit this step when using almonds).","Place remaining pistachio nuts and 30 g of the reserved sugar into mixing bowl and mill <b>15 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add rice flour and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Thoroughly clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert<\/strong> <strong>butterfly<\/strong> <strong>whisk.<\/strong> Place egg whites into mixing bowl and whisk <b>2 min\/37°C\/speed 3.5<b>.","With butterfly whisk still in place, whip <b>3 min\/37°C\/speed 3<b>, slowly add remaining reserved sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid, 1 spoon at a time, until soft peaks form and meringue is glossy. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add vanilla and reserved pistachio and sugar mixture and combine <b>4 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat <b>4 sec\/\/speed 2<b>.","Place a teaspoonful of biscuit mixture onto 1 of the prepared baking trays, then top with a sprinkle of the reserved crushed pistachios (or flaked almonds). Repeat with remaining biscuit mixture to form approx. 20 biscuits and garnish with remaining crushed pistachio nuts (or almonds).","Bake for 9 minutes (180°C) or until browned around the edges. Dust with icing sugar while still warm, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely (approx. 20 minutes) before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g sugar","90 g pistachio nuts, shelled, unsalted","30 g rice flour","2 egg whites","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","2 tbsp icing sugar, for dusting"]}],"id":"r127577","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-RH1a4HCfx5Y\/XZWqCN-Hd1I\/AAAAAAAAfSM\/bUJf028AWZ4h_mtf3xqLy